Photo: XinhuaXi Jinping, general secretary of the Communist Party of China Central Committee, on Wednesday inspected central China's Hunan Province.In the village of Shazhou, Rucheng County, Xi visited places including a revolution-themed exhibition hall, a village service center, a clinic, a modern agricultural tourism demonstration base, a primary school, and the homes of villagers.Xi learned about education on the history of revolution, poverty relief industries, and progress in consolidating poverty eradication. 

